description:
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Following a restructure within our successful Integrated Therapies service we are looking for an experienced Physiotherapist to take on the role of Specialist Physiotherapist in Respiratory Medicine at Colchester Hospital.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The successful applicant will have a clinical caseload on the medical respiratory ward, and at the front door in the High dependency unit of EAU and with respiratory patients presenting to AMSDEC. They would also manage a small team of therapists, assistant staff and students working on the respiratory ward.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are looking for someone with Advanced respiratory skills and NHS experience of working in Respiratory Medicine at Band 6 level or higher as well as appropriate post graduate qualifications ideally at masters level. A current clinical educators course is also required.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;This is a new role so we are also looking for someone with the drive and vision to develop the service.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;This post would include working shifts as part of the 7 day working rota and would include participation in the respiratory on-call list.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Please note that this role is subject to a DBS check which will be charged to the successful candidate. Full details can be found within the ‘DBS Information’ documents attached to this advert.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Christina Richardson, Professional Lead for Physiotherapy at Colchester, on 07825 364377&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
